    "themes_and_goals": "The goal of this course is to improve students’ English conversation skills.  Students should build confidence in their abilities to use English through participating in simple English conversations centered around topics in everyday life and understanding on the basic level words and expressions spoken by native English speakers.  Also, they should learn, through extensive pair-work and group-work, how to ask questions and use expressions for clarification when they don’t understand something.  An important aim of this course is to assist students in building confidence in their English listening and speaking skills. \nこの授業は英会話スキルの向上を目的とします。英語を母国語として話す先生といっしょに、日常生活に根ざした話題の会話をしながら基礎的な語彙・表現を学びます。幅広いペアワークやグループワークを通して、会話中にわからないことがあったときの質問のしかたや相手の言ったことの確認のしかたを学び、英語で聞く・話すことにもっと自信が持てるようになることが重要です。",
    "overview": "Lessons will begin with and introductions of the vocabulary with the subject of the lesson.Then, in the conversation section, students will be presented target language in context. Lessons also include listening activities and communication tasks in pairs and small groups. After speaking and listening activities, students should complete self-study activities to reinforce vocabulary and grammar skills.  \n授業はテキストに沿って、まずそのユニットのテーマに関連する語彙を学びます。次にモデルとなる短い会話を聞いて、重要表現を文脈の中で学びます。さらにペアやグループでさまざまなリスニング、スピーキングの練習をしたり、学習した語彙や文法事項の復習をしたりします。",
